[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This is the eighth recipe in Chapter 11 (Conversational AI / Virtual Assistants) and the chapter's first recipe to combine continuous crisis screening as architectural primitive (every patient utterance, not just first; with C-SSRS / PHQ-9-item-9-adapted validated language; with false-negative-rate as launch-gate metric), explicit non-therapist disclosure refresh as architectural primitive (every session, not just enrollment), companion-pattern avoidance as architectural discipline (forbidden-patterns enforced at system prompt, output safety, persona-and-tone evaluator, sampled review), warm-handoff to licensed clinicians as primary safety architecture (with bridge-and-stay-present pattern, with conversation context attached, with capacity sized to the patient population), therapeutic-content-corpus governance with behavioral-health-clinical-leadership ownership (CBT, behavioral activation, DBT skills, mindfulness, distress tolerance, sleep hygiene, journaling prompts, condition-specific psychoeducation, with defined indications and contraindications, with clinical-leadership signoff as launch gate), mandatory-reporting routing for sensitive disclosures (child abuse, elder abuse, IPV, certain mental-health crisis types, with state-specific routing), mental-health-specific privacy-and-consent posture (state-specific mental-health-record statutes that exceed HIPAA baseline, 42 CFR Part 2 for substance-use treatment data, separately-keyed sensitive-disclosure surface), FDA-strategy alignment as architectural constraint (patient-facing mental-health software with therapeutic claims sits squarely on the SaMD line; the institution's FDA-experienced regulatory counsel is involved from architectural design), safety-plan integration with FHIR CarePlan (Stanley-Brown safety planning intervention or similar evidence-based template, instantiated per patient with their clinician), eligibility-check-and-off-ramp for excluded populations (primary psychotic-spectrum diagnoses, active inpatient or residential treatment, primary substance-use disorder requiring specialized treatment, minors in adult-only deployments), and population-specific calibration (anxiety-focused, depression-focused, substance-use-disorder, eating-disorder, PTSD-stabilization, postpartum, workplace, college, older-adult, voice-channel, multi-language). It establishes the chapter's mental-health-acuity-acute discipline (the recipe is the chapter's first recipe with explicit life-safety stakes) and frames the chapter's posture toward patient-facing mental-health AI as patient-safety-acute clinical software with explicit ethical and regulatory engineering, distinguishing the careful end of the spectrum from the AI-companion category that has produced documented harm.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The opening Sam-at-11:47-PM-Wednesday vignette earns its position as the chapter's strongest single articulation of the activation-energy-too-high failure mode in mental-health crisis. The "the safety plan is in the drawer and not in Sam's hand" framing, the "I'm a chat tool, not a person, but I'm going to stay with you while we figure out the next step. Before anything else, I want to ask you something directly: are you having any thoughts of hurting yourself right now?" example dialog, the warm-handoff-to-Priya-the-licensed-counselor pivot, the "Sam goes to sleep at 1:14 AM. Sam is alive in the morning" closing, and the contrast with "the typical outcome" enumeration are operationally accurate and recipe-distinct. The "this is a good outcome. It is not a typical outcome" pivot into the millions-of-Americans-who-experience-mental-health-crisis-between-visits framing is the recipe's strongest single passage on the gap-between-what-the-population-needs-and-what-the-system-delivers primitive. The eight not-this enumerations (not a therapist, not a friend, not a substitute for clinical care, not a crisis-line replacement, not a one-size-fits-all product, not a regulatory afterthought, not a quick win, with the recipe-distinct "not a friend" framing as architectural discipline rather than just a marketing claim) are the recipe's clearest articulation of the bot-scope-as-discipline primitive in mental-health context.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Technology section is the chapter's introductory pedagogy on mental-health-support-as-structured-content-delivery-with-crisis-screening-and-warm-handoff and executes at the right grain. The "Why Mental Health Has Resisted Digital Tools, and Why The Latest Attempts Are Different" subsection grounds the engagement-attrition-and-therapeutic-relationship-as-active-ingredient failure modes in specific architectural diagnoses, with the references to the three-wave history (self-guided CBT 2010-2017, teletherapy 2017-2022, conversational AI 2022-) appropriately TODO-hedged. The careful-end-vs-middle-vs-risky-end-of-spectrum framing is the recipe's clearest articulation of the architectural-decisions-determine-which-end-of-spectrum-the-product-lives-on primitive. The "What a Mental-Health Support Bot Actually Does" subsection's nine-task-surface decomposition (onboarding and disclosure, crisis screening up front and continuously, patient-initiated conversations within scope, structured therapeutic-content delivery, mood and symptom tracking, safety-plan integration, warm handoff to licensed clinicians, care-team reporting with consent, long-term relationship maintenance, off-boarding) is correctly granular and recipe-distinct. The "Why a Generic LLM Cannot Run a Mental-Health Support Bot" subsection's thirteen-property enumeration (no consistent crisis screening, no scope discipline about therapy, invents clinical content when grounding is weak, no theory of harmful-coping-strategy detection, no theory of when not to engage, has companion-pattern drift, has clinical-decision-rule arithmetic problems for screening instruments, has compliance implications specific to mental health, no theory of mandatory reporting, no theory of when patient is in active emergency, no theory of relationship-quality boundaries, no theory of parasocial-companion-pattern-as-failure-mode, no theory of when to end a conversation) is recipe-distinct and earns its position as the recipe's clearest articulation of the why-naked-LLM-in-front-of-mental-health-support-is-not-a-mental-health-support-tool primitive. The "What the Mental-Health Bot Has To Do That the Previous Bots Did Not" subsection's eight-structural-commitments enumeration (crisis screening as architectural primitive, therapeutic-content discipline with clinical-leadership ownership, explicit non-therapist disclosure as architectural primitive, warm handoff to licensed clinicians as primary safety architecture, mandatory-reporting routing, companion-pattern avoidance as architectural discipline, privacy and consent posture calibrated for mental-health data, FDA-strategy alignment as architectural constraint) is the recipe's clearest articulation of the mental-health-bot-vs-other-chapter-11-bots-distinction primitive. The "Mental-Health Reality" subsection's twelve-property enumeration is the recipe's most-distinctive contribution.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The ten-stage architecture (enrollment and consent, longitudinal-store initialization, channel entry with disclosure, input safety with continuous crisis screening, identity-and-context loading with safety-plan retrieval, conversation handling with therapeutic-content-grounded responses, output safety with companion-pattern detection, warm-handoff routing, care-team reporting with consent enforcement, audit logging with mental-health-specific retention) is the right shape and recipe-distinct from 11.7's eleven-stage decomposition. The five new architectural primitives (continuous crisis-screening pipeline, therapeutic-content-corpus governance, companion-pattern avoidance discipline, warm-handoff infrastructure with capacity sizing, mental-health-specific privacy-and-consent posture) are correctly elevated. The recipe-distinct cross-cutting design points (continuous crisis screening as architectural primitive, therapeutic-content-corpus governance with behavioral-health-clinical-leadership ownership, companion-pattern avoidance as architectural discipline, warm-handoff infrastructure with capacity sizing, mental-health-specific privacy and consent posture, mandatory-reporting routing, FDA-strategy alignment as architectural constraint, citation discipline as architectural primitive, conservative-bias-default policy, per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable, disaster-recovery topology) are correctly elevated.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Why-These-Services section walks each AWS component back to the conceptual primitive it implements. The Honest Take is exceptionally strong, with twelve traps earning the recipe's voice: institutional-content-as-someone-else's-problem recast as therapeutic-content-library-as-the-product with multi-quarter-clinical-content-investment; crisis-screening-as-feature-rather-than-architectural-floor; companion-pattern-drift; warm-handoff-workforce-sizing; scope-discipline-with-the-bot-that-drifts-into-therapy framing; regulatory-positioning; privacy-posture; consent-gating-for-care-team-sharing; eligibility-check-and-off-ramp; relationship-quality-engineering; engagement-attrition-focus; equity-gap. The "thing that surprises engineers" / "thing that surprises clinical leaders" / "thing that surprises business leaders" cross-discipline-comparisons earn their positions. The closing "the mental-health support bot is the recipe in this chapter where the consequences of getting it wrong are most severe, the discipline required to get it right is the highest, and the temptation to over-extend the bot's scope is the most dangerous" framing is the recipe's strongest single closing primitive, and the "if the institutional commitment to those harder parts is not present, the right answer is not to ship a less-careful version; the right answer is not to ship" actionable takeaway earns its position as the chapter's strongest analog of the self-deprecating-expertise-with-don't-ship-it register.
